ewcommand{\MGF}{	ext{MGF}}$ MGF of Normal Distribution For $X\sim\N(\mu,\sigma^2)$, we have $\MGF(	heta)=\exp(	heta\mu + 	heta^2\sigma^2/2)$. We have $\E(X^k) = \MGF^{\ (k)}(0)$. Truncated Normal Distribution Consider a two-sided truncation $(a,b)$ on $\N(\mu,\sigma^2)$, then $$ \E[X\mid a &lt; X &lt; b] = \mu - \sigma rac{\phi(\alpha) - \phi( eta)}{\Phi(\alpha) - \Phi( eta)} $$
